value.value: A lymph node located in the area around the hilum of an organ.
The section of the left circumflex coronary artery that arises from the left main coronary artery and extends to the first marginal branch.
A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the second digit of the hand or foot connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.
A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the third digit of the hand or foot connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.
A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the fourth digit of the hand or foot connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.
A ginglymoid (hinge) synovial joint within the fifth digit of the hand or foot connecting the proximal and middle phalanges.
The section of the left anterior descending coronary artery that arises from the left main coronary artery and extends to the first diagonal branch.
The section of the right coronary artery proximal to the origin of the right ventricular artery.
An artery that arises from the left main coronary artery and is positioned between the left anterior descending coronary artery and the circumflex artery.
The innermost layer of endothelial cells and connective tissue that lines the right atrium.
A regimen consisting of vinblastine, dactinomycin, bleomycin, cyclophosphamide and cisplatin that may be used in the treatment of testicular cancer.

label.value: Right Coronary Artery and its Branches

value.value: The right coronary artery and all of its branches, including the right posterior descending, right posterolateral and acute marginal branches.
The arterial branch between the right posterior descending artery segment and the first right posterolateral segment.

In an individual with a right-dominant heart, the arterial branch that arises from the distal right coronary artery between the acute marginal artery and the first right posterolateral segment. It supplies the inferior apex of the heart.
The innermost layer of endothelial cells and connective tissue that lines the right ventricle.
The second artery arising from the left anterior descending (LAD) artery that supplies the anterolateral wall, when counted from proximal to distal.

In an individual with a left-dominant heart, this is the second branch that arises from the circumflex artery atrioventricular groove continuation when counted from proximal to distal. It supplies the posterolateral wall.
The second artery arising from the left circumflex artery that supplies the lateral wall, when counted from proximal to distal.

In an individual with a right-dominant heart, this is the second branch that arises from the right coronary artery distal to the right posterior descending artery, when counted from proximal to distal.
The arteries arising from the right posterior descending artery that supply the interventricular septum.
The area directly beneath the tongue.
The third artery arising from the left anterior descending (LAD) artery that supplies the anterolateral wall, when counted from proximal to distal.
The third artery arising from the left circumflex artery that supplies the lateral wall, when counted from proximal to distal.

In an individual with a left-dominant heart, this is the third branch that arises from the circumflex artery atrioventricular groove continuation when counted from proximal to distal. It supplies the posterolateral wall.

In an individual with a right-dominant heart, this is the third branch that arises from the right coronary artery distal to the right posterior descending artery, when counted from proximal to distal.
A combination of syndesmosis and synovial joints formed by the articulation of the talus with the navicular and the calcaneus with the cuboid.

label.value: Study Subject Withdrawal by Parent or Guardian

value.value: An indication that a study participant has been removed from the study by the parent or legal guardian.

label.value: Accumulation Ratio Area Under the Curve

value.value: The area under the curve (AUCTAU) at steady state divided by the area under the curve over the initial dosing interval.
The maximum concentration at steady state divided by the maximum concentration during the initial dosing interval.
The minimum concentration at steady state divided by the minimum concentration during the initial dosing interval.

label.value: Amount Recovered from T1 to T2

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type over the interval from T1 to T2.

label.value: Amount Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC over the interval from T1 to T2 divided by body mass index.

label.value: Amount Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC over the interval from T1 to T2 divided by surface area.

label.value: Amount Recovered from T1 to T2 Normalized by Weight

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC over the interval from T1 to T2 divided by weight.
The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type between doses (TAU).

label.value: Amount Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC between doses (TAU) divided by body mass index.

label.value: Amount Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC between doses (TAU) divided by surface area.

label.value: Amount Recovered Over Dosing Interval Normalized by Weight

value.value: The cumulative amount recovered from the specimen type specified in PPSPEC between doses (TAU) divided by weight.

label.value: Concentration Divided by Body Mass Index

value.value: The concentration divided by body mass index.
The concentration divided by dose.
The concentration divided by surface area.
The concentration divided by weight.
The initial volume of distribution for a substance administered by bolus intravascular dosing.

label.value: Initial Volume of Distribution Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The initial volume of distribution for a substance administered by bolus intravascular dosing divided by the body mass index.

label.value: Initial Volume of Distribution Normalized by Dose

value.value: The initial volume of distribution for a substance administered by bolus intravascular dosing divided by the dose.

label.value: Initial Volume of Distribution Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The initial volume of distribution for a substance administered by bolus intravascular dosing divided by the surface area.

label.value: Initial Volume of Distribution Normalized by Weight

value.value: The initial volume of distribution for a substance administered by bolus intravascular dosing divided by the weight.
